Revision of the world species of Zambion (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Tryphoninae)Abstract The world species of Zambion Kasparyan (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Tryphoninae) are revised including re-descriptions of Zambion monodon Kasparyan and Zambion hirtum Delobel. Five new species are described: Zambion kasparyani sp. n., Zambion rogeri sp. n., Zambion eileenae sp. n., Zambion wahli sp. n. andZambion broadi sp. n. A key to species is provided. The genus is endemic to Africa (Angola to Kenya) and is one of only three genera of the tribe Tryphonini recorded from the Afrotropical region.